  "prompt": "Can a Guitar Hero guitar be used in Rock Band?",
  "response": "Yes, a **Guitar Hero guitar** can generally be used in **Rock Band**, but there are some important factors to consider based on the specific platforms and game versions:\n\n### **Compatibility by Platform**:\n1. **Xbox 360**  \n   - Guitar Hero controllers for Xbox 360 are compatible with Rock Band and most Rock Band peripherals are compatible with Guitar Hero.  \n   - Microsoft\u2019s standard for controllers ensures cross-compatibility for most instruments.  \n\n2. **PlayStation 3**  \n   - Guitar Hero guitars work with Rock Band on PS3, but you may need to sync the controller properly.  \n   - Some older Guitar Hero controllers might require additional setup or configurations.  \n\n3. **Wii**  \n   - On the Wii, Guitar Hero and Rock Band instruments are generally cross-compatible due to the same control scheme.  \n   - However, Rock Band 1 instruments do not work with Wii games, so check the specific game and controller generation.  \n\n4. **PC**  \n   - Compatibility depends on your setup. You may need adapters or third-party software (like **Clone Hero**) to use Guitar Hero guitars with Rock Band on PC.  \n\n### **Limitations**:\n- **Button Layout**: Guitar Hero guitars have a slightly different button layout compared to Rock Band guitars, which might affect gameplay or feel.  \n- **Whammy Bar and Tilt Sensor**: These features should work, though Rock Band and Guitar Hero handle them differently in certain songs.  \n- **Wireless vs. Wired**: Make sure the controller is correctly synced or connected to the console.  \n\n### **Testing**:\nIf you\u2019re unsure, test your Guitar Hero controller with your Rock Band game to confirm functionality. Most players find that the transition is seamless with minimal adjustments.  \n\nLet me know if you need further details! \ud83c\udfb8",
